### Standard enthalpy change of combustion, \(\Delta H_{c}^{\bullet}\)

The standard enthalpy change of combustion is the _energy released_ when _one mole_ of a substance is _completely burnt_ in excess oxygen at 298 K and 1 bar.

### C(s) + O\({}_{2}\)(g) \(\rightarrow\) CO\({}_{2}\)(g) \(\Delta H_{c}^{\bullet}=-393\) kJ mol-1

393 kJ of energy is released when 1 mole of carbon (graphite) is burnt in excess oxygen under standard conditions of 298 K and 1 bar.

