### Ionisation Energy, _I.E._

First ionisation energy (1\({}^{\rm st}\) _I.E._) of an element is the energy absorbed to remove one mole of most loosely held electrons from one mole of gaseous atoms to form one mole of gaseous single positively charged cations.

