### Electron Affinity, _E.A._

First electron affinity (1\({}^{\rm st}\) _E.A._) of an element is the energy released when one mole of gaseous atoms gain one mole of electrons to form one mole of gaseous single negatively charged anions.

\begin{tabular}{l l} E.g. & O\({}^{-}\)(g) + e\({}^{-}\)\(\longrightarrow\) O\({}^{2-}\)(g) & 2\({}^{\rm nd}\) _E.A._ of O = +790 kJ mol\({}^{-1}\) \\ \end{tabular}

