### Lattice Energy, _I.E._

Lattice energy (_I.E._) of an ionic compound is the energy released when one mole of ionic solid is formed from its constituent gaseous ions.

\begin{tabular}{l l} E.g. & Na\({}^{+}\)(g) + C\({}^{+}\)(g) \(\longrightarrow\) NaC(s) & _I.E._ (NaC/) = -776 kJ mol\({}^{-1}\) \\ \end{tabular}

